---
description: Delegation transparency and closeout reporting
alwaysApply: true
---

For non-trivial tasks, final responses must include a structured closeout with delegation transparency.

## Required closeout sections
- task summary (`task_id`, risk tier, change type, acceptance criteria status)
- delegation ledger (who was delegated, why, outcome used/rejected)
- skipped specialist rationale (and compensating controls)
- conflicts and resolution decisions
- verification evidence and final verifier status
- residual risk statement
- tokens/cost/time summary when available
- follow-up items

## Delegation discipline
- do not delegate only for optics; every delegation must have expected value
- when a required specialist is skipped, explicitly explain why and what replaced that control
- for high-risk tasks, unresolved specialist conflicts must block finalization

## Artifact placement
- temporary governance artifacts, plans, and working notes must be kept under `tmp/`
